()IdentityAttributeDefinition kya hai?
--🔹 1️⃣ IdentityAttributeDefinition kya hai?
👉 IdentityAttributeDefinition = attribute ka “rule / metadata / configuration”
Matlab:-
IdentityAttribute = actual value (email = rahul@gmail.com)
IdentityAttributeDefinition = us attribute ka structure aur rules.

✅ Example:-
Attribute	  Value	                        Definition
email:----rahul@gmail.com:-----------String, required, read-only
department:-----IT:----------------------String,editable 
age:------------25:------------------------Integer, required

🔹 2️⃣ Ye kya karta hai?
👉 Ye define karta hai:-
attribute ka type (String, Boolean, Number)
attribute mandatory hai ya nahi
attribute editable hai ya read-only
UI me kaise dikhega

🔹 3️⃣ Kya ye DB me store hota hai?
✅ Haan bhai, ye bhi DB me store hota hai
📦 Difference:-
Identity → user data
AttributeDefinition → system configuration

🔹 4️⃣ Important Fields:-
Field	        Meaning
name:---------attribute ka naam
type:---------data type (String, Boolean, etc.)
required:-----mandatory hai ya nahi
readOnly:-----edit allowed hai ya nahi
multiValued:--ek se zyada value allowed
displayName:--UI me naam
description:--explanation

🔹 5️⃣ Important Methods:-
🔸 Basic:-
getName()
setName(String name)
getDisplayName()
setDisplayName(String displayName)
getDescription()
setDescription(String description)

🔸 Type & Format:-
getType()
setType(Class type)
getFormat()
setFormat(String format)

🔸 Validation:-
isRequired()
setRequired(boolean required)
isMultiValued()
setMultiValued(boolean multiValued)

🔸 Access Control:-
isReadOnly()
setReadOnly(boolean readOnly)
isHidden()
setHidden(boolean hidden)

🔸 Utility:-
toString()
equals(Object obj)
hashCode()
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🚀 🔥 IdentityAttributeDefinition Full Code (One Page)
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointFactory;
import sailpoint.object.IdentityAttributeDefinition;

public class IdentityAttrDefExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        // 🔹 1️⃣ Get SailPoint Context
        SailPointContext context = SailPointFactory.getCurrentContext();

        // 🔹 2️⃣ Create Definition Object
        IdentityAttributeDefinition def = new IdentityAttributeDefinition();

        // =========================
        // 🔸 Basic
        // =========================
        def.setName("email");
        def.setDisplayName("Email Address");
        def.setDescription("User email attribute");

        System.out.println("Name: " + def.getName());
        System.out.println("DisplayName: " + def.getDisplayName());
        System.out.println("Description: " + def.getDescription());

        // =========================
        // 🔸 Type & Format
        // =========================
        def.setType(String.class);
        def.setFormat("email");

        System.out.println("Type: " + def.getType());
        System.out.println("Format: " + def.getFormat());

        // =========================
        // 🔸 Validation
        // =========================
        def.setRequired(true);
        def.setMultiValued(false);

        System.out.println("Required: " + def.isRequired());
        System.out.println("MultiValued: " + def.isMultiValued());

        // =========================
        // 🔸 Access Control
        // =========================
        def.setReadOnly(false);
        def.setHidden(false);

        System.out.println("ReadOnly: " + def.isReadOnly());
        System.out.println("Hidden: " + def.isHidden());

        // =========================
        // 🔸 Utility Methods
        // =========================
        System.out.println("toString(): " + def.toString());

        IdentityAttributeDefinition def2 = new IdentityAttributeDefinition();
        def2.setName("email");

        System.out.println("equals(): " + def.equals(def2));
        System.out.println("hashCode(): " + def.hashCode());

        // 🔹 3️⃣ Save in DB (optional)
        context.saveObject(def);
        context.commitTransaction();

        System.out.println("✅ Definition Saved Successfully");
    }
}
📤 🔥 Output Example
Name: email
DisplayName: Email Address
Description: User email attribute

Type: class java.lang.String
Format: email

Required: true
MultiValued: false

ReadOnly: false
Hidden: false

toString(): IdentityAttributeDefinition[email]
equals(): true
hashCode(): 12345678

✅ Definition Saved Successfully